01:17:43.380 --> 01:17:46.290
that I've been really
lucky to be able to write

01:17:46.290 --> 01:17:48.950
in Ukrainian language,
because, well,

01:17:48.950 --> 01:17:53.630
once they measured the beauty
of languages, I have no idea,

01:17:53.630 --> 01:17:56.650
some British people, like
British [inaudible] did this.

01:17:56.650 --> 01:18:02.060
So, Ukrainian [inaudible]
the second place in the list

01:18:02.060 --> 01:18:04.310
of most beautiful
languages after the Italian.

01:18:04.310 --> 01:18:10.220
I must admit, this language
is then cool for writing.

01:18:10.220 --> 01:18:12.290
It is very flexible.

01:18:12.290 --> 01:18:17.970
The syntaxes is so that you can
like twist it anyway you need.

01:18:17.970 --> 01:18:21.120
You can put a lot of double
sentences, and triple sentences,

01:18:21.120 --> 01:18:24.670
and play with the
language and make it funny.

01:18:24.670 --> 01:18:27.440
And, also, you can play a
lot with [inaudible] sound

01:18:27.440 --> 01:18:29.950
and with the order of
words and sentences.

01:18:29.950 --> 01:18:33.080
So, I guess, one of
the best instruments

01:18:33.080 --> 01:18:37.960
for writing one can get,
so why wouldn't I use it?

